net.minecraftforge.common.config

接口 IFieldWrapper

  • 所有已知实现类:
    FieldWrapper

    public interface IFieldWrapper
    The objects are expected to get their wrapped field, the owning class, instance and category string on initialization. In general: The key is the fully qualified property name, where each subcategory is appended with a dot. i.e: general.map.isPresent

      • getTypeAdapter

        net.minecraftforge.common.config.ITypeAdapter getTypeAdapter()
        返回:

      • getKeys

        java.lang.String[] getKeys()
        返回:

      • hasKey

        boolean hasKey(java.lang.String key)
        参数:
        key - a fully qualified property key
        返回:
        true if the wrapped field contains a property associated with the given key

      • handlesKey

        boolean handlesKey(java.lang.String key)
        参数:
        key - a fully qualified property key
        返回:
        true if the wrapped field can save information associated with the given key, false otherwise

      • setupConfiguration

        default void setupConfiguration(Configuration cfg,
                                java.lang.String desc,
                                java.lang.String langKey,
                                boolean reqMCRestart,
                                boolean reqWorldRestart,
                                boolean hasSlidingControl)
        参数:
        cfg - The configuration object holding the properties
        desc - The properties description
        langKey - The languageKey of the property, used in GUI
        reqMCRestart - True, if a change in this property requires a restart of Minecraft
        reqWorldRestart - True, if the world needs to be reloaded after changes to this property
        hasSlidingControl - true if the property is going to have a slider control attached in the configuration UI; works in conjunction with Config.RangeInt and Config.RangeDouble

      • getCategory

        java.lang.String getCategory()
        i.e. general.map in the example above
        返回:
        the category name in which the entries should be saved. This includes the parent categories
